		<item>
		<title>
		By: Paul		</title>
		<link>https://www.ultrasaurus.com/2008/12/rails-2-day-4-rcov-and-more-behavior-driven-development/#comment-354</link>

		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Paul]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 20 Jan 2009 06:25:44 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.ultrasaurus.com/sarahblog/2008/12/rails-2-day-4-rcov-and-more-behavior-driven-development/#comment-354</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Hi.
This is a great post. I have a couple small suggestions:

change this &lt;code&gt;&#060;tr id=&quot;&#060;%=&quot;task&quot;+task.id.to_s%&#062;&quot;&#062;&lt;/code&gt;
to this &lt;code&gt;&#060;tr id=&quot;&#060;%= dom_id(task) %&#062;&quot;&#062;&lt;/code&gt;

That will produce output like task_1, task_2, etc. That&#039;s just a bit more of a &quot;Rails&quot; way to do it.

Then in your matcher, you could change this &lt;code&gt;within(&quot;table &#062; tr#task&quot;+task.id.to_s) do&lt;/code&gt;
to this &lt;code&gt;within(&quot;table &#062; tr#task_#{task.id}&quot;) do&lt;/code&gt;

Or you could include &lt;code&gt;ActionView::Helpers::RecordIdentificationHelper&lt;/code&gt; and then change it to this &lt;code&gt;within(&quot;table &#062; tr##{dom_id task}&quot;) do&lt;/code&gt;

Cheers]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Hi.<br />
This is a great post. I have a couple small suggestions:</p>
<p>change this <code>&lt;tr id="&lt;%="task"+task.id.to_s%&gt;"&gt;</code><br />
to this <code>&lt;tr id="&lt;%= dom_id(task) %&gt;"&gt;</code></p>
<p>That will produce output like task_1, task_2, etc. That&#8217;s just a bit more of a &#8220;Rails&#8221; way to do it.</p>
<p>Then in your matcher, you could change this <code>within("table &gt; tr#task"+task.id.to_s) do</code><br />
to this <code>within("table &gt; tr#task_#{task.id}") do</code></p>
<p>Or you could include <code>ActionView::Helpers::RecordIdentificationHelper</code> and then change it to this <code>within("table &gt; tr##{dom_id task}") do</code></p>
<p>Cheers</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
